#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:1
msgid ""
"This is a walkthrough of the NumPy 2.4.0 release on Linux, which will be the "
"first feature release using the `numpy/numpy-release <https://github.com/"
"numpy/numpy-release>`__ repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:5
msgid ""
"The commands can be copied into the command line, but be sure to replace "
"2.4.0 with the correct version. This should be read together with the :ref:"
"`general release guide <prepare_release>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:10
msgid "Facility preparation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:12
msgid ""
"Before beginning to make a release, use the ``requirements/*_requirements."
"txt`` files to ensure that you have the needed software. Most software can "
"be installed with pip, but some will require apt-get, dnf, or whatever your "
"system uses for software. You will also need a GitHub personal access token "
"(PAT) to push the documentation. There are a few ways to streamline things:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:18
msgid ""
"Git can be set up to use a keyring to store your GitHub personal access "
"token. Search online for the details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:23
msgid "Prior to release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:26
msgid "Add/drop Python versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:28
msgid ""
"When adding or dropping Python versions, multiple config and CI files need "
"to be edited in addition to changing the minimum version in ``pyproject."
"toml``. Make these changes in an ordinary PR against main and backport if "
"necessary. We currently release wheels for new Python versions after the "
"first Python RC once manylinux and cibuildwheel support that new Python "
"version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:36
msgid "Backport pull requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:38
msgid ""
"Changes that have been marked for this release must be backported to the "
"maintenance/2.4.x branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:43
msgid "Update 2.4.0 milestones"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:45
msgid ""
"Look at the issues/prs with 2.4.0 milestones and either push them off to a "
"later version, or maybe remove the milestone. You may need to add a "
"milestone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:49
msgid "Check the numpy-release repo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:51
msgid ""
"The things to check are the ``cibuildwheel`` version in ``.github/workflows/"
"wheels.yml`` and the ``openblas`` versions in ``openblas_requirements.txt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:57
msgid "Make a release PR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:59
msgid ""
"Four documents usually need to be updated or created for the release PR:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:61
msgid "The changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:62
msgid "The release notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:63
msgid "The ``.mailmap`` file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:64
msgid "The ``pyproject.toml`` file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:66
msgid ""
"These changes should be made in an ordinary PR against the maintenance "
"branch. Other small, miscellaneous fixes may be part of this PR. The commit "
"message might be something like::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:70
msgid ""
"REL: Prepare for the NumPy 2.4.0 release\n"
"\n"
"- Create 2.4.0-changelog.rst.\n"
"- Update 2.4.0-notes.rst.\n"
"- Update .mailmap.\n"
"- Update pyproject.toml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:79
msgid "Set the release version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:81
msgid ""
"Check the ``pyproject.toml`` file and set the release version and update the "
"classifier if needed::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:84
#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:290
msgid "$ gvim pyproject.toml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:88
msgid "Check the ``doc/source/release.rst`` file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:90
msgid ""
"make sure that the release notes have an entry in the ``release.rst`` file::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:92
#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:286
msgid "$ gvim doc/source/release.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:96
msgid "Generate the changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:98
msgid ""
"The changelog is generated using the changelog tool (``spin changelog``), "
"which collects merged pull requests and formats them into a release-ready "
"changelog::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:102
msgid ""
"$ spin changelog $GITHUB v2.3.0..maintenance/2.4.x > doc/changelog/2.4.0-"
"changelog.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:104
msgid ""
"where ``GITHUB`` contains your GitHub access token. The text will need to be "
"checked for non-standard contributor names. It is also a good idea to remove "
"any links that may be present in the PR titles as they don't translate well "
"to Markdown, replace them with monospaced text. The non-standard contributor "
"names should be fixed by updating the ``.mailmap`` file, which is a lot of "
"work. It is best to make several trial runs before reaching this point and "
"ping the malefactors using a GitHub issue to get the needed information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:114
msgid "Finish the release notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:116
msgid ""
"If there are any release notes snippets in ``doc/release/upcoming_changes/"
"``, run ``spin notes``, which will incorporate the snippets into the ``doc/"
"source/release/notes-towncrier.rst`` file and delete the snippets::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:120
msgid ""
"$ spin notes\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release/notes-towncrier.rst doc/source/release/2.4.0-notes."
"rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:123
msgid ""
"Once the ``notes-towncrier`` contents have been incorporated into release "
"notes the ``.. include:: notes-towncrier.rst`` directive can be removed.  "
"The notes will always need some fixups, the introduction will need to be "
"written, and significant changes should be called out. For patch releases "
"the changelog text may also be appended, but not for the initial release as "
"it is too long. Check previous release notes to see how this is done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:132
msgid "Test the wheel builds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:134
msgid ""
"After the release PR is merged, go to the ``numpy-release`` repository in "
"your browser and manually trigger the workflow on the ``maintenance/2.4.x`` "
"branch using the ``Run workflow`` button in ``actions``.  Make sure that the "
"upload target is ``none`` in the *environment* dropdown. The wheels take "
"about 1 hour to build, but sometimes GitHub is very slow. If some wheel "
"builds fail for unrelated reasons, you can re-run them as normal in the "
"GitHub Actions UI with ``re-run failed``. After the wheels are built review "
"the results, checking that the number of artifacts are correct, the wheel "
"names are as expected, etc. If everything looks good, proceed with the "
"release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:146
msgid "Release walkthrough"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:148
msgid ""
"Note that in the code snippets below, ``upstream`` refers to the root "
"repository on GitHub and ``origin`` to its fork in your personal GitHub "
"repositories. You may need to make adjustments if you have not forked the "
"repository but simply cloned it locally. You can also edit ``.git/config`` "
"and add ``upstream`` if it isn't already present."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:156
msgid "1. Tag the release commit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:158
msgid ""
"Checkout the branch for the release, make sure it is up to date, and clean "
"the repository::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:161
msgid ""
"$ git checkout maintenance/2.4.x\n"
"$ git pull upstream maintenance/2.4.x\n"
"$ git submodule update\n"
"$ git clean -xdfq"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:166
msgid "Sanity check::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:168
msgid "$ python3 -m spin test -m full"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:170
msgid ""
"Tag the release and push the tag. This requires write permission for the "
"numpy repository::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:173
msgid ""
"$ git tag -a -s v2.4.0 -m\"NumPy 2.4.0 release\"\n"
"$ git push upstream v2.4.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:176
msgid "If you need to delete the tag due to error::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:178
msgid ""
"$ git tag -d v2.4.0\n"
"$ git push --delete upstream v2.4.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:183
msgid "2. Build wheels and sdist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:185
msgid ""
"Go to the ``numpy-release`` repository in your browser and manually trigger "
"the workflow on the ``maintenance/2.4.x`` branch using the ``Run workflow`` "
"button in ``actions``.  Make sure that the upload target is ``pypi`` in the "
"*environment* dropdown. The wheels take about 1 hour to build, but sometimes "
"GitHub is very slow. If some wheel builds fail for unrelated reasons, you "
"can re-run them as normal in the GitHub Actions UI with ``re-run failed``. "
"After the wheels are built review the results, checking that the number of "
"artifacts are correct, the wheel names are as expected, etc. If everything "
"looks good trigger the upload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:197
msgid "3. Upload files to GitHub Releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:199
msgid ""
"Go to `<https://github.com/numpy/numpy/releases>`_, there should be a "
"``v2.4.0`` tag, click on it and hit the edit button for that tag and update "
"the title to \"v2.4.0 (<date>)\". There are two ways to add files, using an "
"editable text window and as binary uploads. The text window needs markdown, "
"so translate the release notes from rst to md::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:205
msgid "$ python tools/write_release.py 2.4.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:207
msgid ""
"this will create a ``release/README.md`` file that you can edit. Check the "
"result to see that it looks correct. Things that may need fixing: wrapped "
"lines that need unwrapping and links that should be changed to monospaced "
"text. Then copy the contents to the clipboard and paste them into the text "
"window. It may take several tries to get it look right. Then"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:213
msgid ""
"Download the sdist (``numpy-2.4.0.tar.gz``) from PyPI and upload it to "
"GitHub as a binary file. You cannot do this using pip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:215
msgid "Upload ``release/README.rst`` as a binary file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:216
msgid "Upload ``doc/changelog/2.4.0-changelog.rst`` as a binary file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:217
msgid "Check the pre-release button if this is a pre-releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:218
msgid "Hit the ``Publish release`` button at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:221
msgid ""
"Please ensure that all 3 files are uploaded are present and the release text "
"is complete. Releases are configured to be immutable, so mistakes can't "
"(easily) be fixed anymore."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:227
msgid "4. Upload documents to numpy.org (skip for prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:229
msgid "You will need a GitHub personal access token to push the update."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:231
msgid ""
"This step is only needed for final releases and can be skipped for pre-"
"releases and most patch releases. ``make merge-doc`` clones the ``numpy/"
"doc`` repo into ``doc/build/merge`` and updates it with the new "
"documentation::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:235
msgid ""
"$ git clean -xdfq\n"
"$ git co v2.4.0\n"
"$ rm -rf doc/build  # want version to be current\n"
"$ python -m spin docs merge-doc --build\n"
"$ pushd doc/build/merge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:241
msgid ""
"If the release series is a new one, you will need to add a new section to "
"the ``doc/build/merge/index.html`` front page just after the \"insert here\" "
"comment::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:244
msgid "$ gvim index.html +/'insert here'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:246
msgid ""
"Further, update the version-switcher json file to add the new release and "
"update the version marked ``(stable)`` and ``preferred``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:249
msgid "$ gvim _static/versions.json"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:251
msgid "Then run ``update.py`` to update the version in ``_static``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:253
msgid "$ python3 update.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:255
msgid ""
"You can \"test run\" the new documentation in a browser to make sure the "
"links work, although the version dropdown will not change, it pulls its "
"information from ``numpy.org``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:259
msgid "$ firefox index.html  # or google-chrome, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:261
msgid "Update the stable link and update::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:263
msgid ""
"$ ln -sfn 2.4 stable\n"
"$ ls -l  # check the link"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:266
msgid ""
"Once everything seems satisfactory, update, commit and upload the changes::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:268
msgid ""
"$ git commit -a -m\"Add documentation for v2.4.0\"\n"
"$ git push git@github.com:numpy/doc\n"
"$ popd"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:274
msgid ""
"5. Reset the maintenance branch into a development state (skip for "
"prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:276
msgid ""
"Create release notes for next release and edit them to set the version. "
"These notes will be a skeleton and have little content::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:279
msgid ""
"$ git checkout -b begin-2.4.1 maintenance/2.4.x\n"
"$ cp doc/source/release/template.rst doc/source/release/2.4.1-notes.rst\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release/2.4.1-notes.rst\n"
"$ git add doc/source/release/2.4.1-notes.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:284
msgid "Add a link to the new release notes::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:288
msgid "Update the ``version`` in ``pyproject.toml``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:292
msgid ""
"Commit the result, edit the commit message, note the files in the commit, "
"and add a line ``[skip cirrus] [skip actions]``, then push::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:295
msgid ""
"$ git commit -a -m\"MAINT: Prepare 2.4.x for further development\"\n"
"$ git rebase -i HEAD^\n"
"$ git push origin HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:299
msgid "Go to GitHub and make a PR. It should be merged quickly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:303
msgid "6. Announce the release on numpy.org (skip for prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:305
msgid ""
"This assumes that you have forked `<https://github.com/numpy/numpy.org>`_::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:307
msgid ""
"$ cd ../numpy.org\n"
"$ git checkout main\n"
"$ git pull upstream main\n"
"$ git checkout -b announce-numpy-2.4.0\n"
"$ gvim content/en/news.md"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:313
msgid ""
"For all releases, go to the bottom of the page and add a one line link. Look "
"to the previous links for example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:315
msgid "For the ``*.0`` release in a cycle:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:317
msgid ""
"Add a new section at the top with a short description of the new features "
"and point the news link to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:319
msgid "Edit the newsHeader and date fields at the top of news.md"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:320
msgid "Also edit the buttonText on line 14 in content/en/config.yaml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:322
msgid "commit and push::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:324
msgid ""
"$ git commit -a -m\"announce the NumPy 2.4.0 release\"\n"
"$ git push origin HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:327
#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:355
msgid "Go to GitHub and make a PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:331
msgid "7. Announce to mailing lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:333
msgid ""
"The release should be announced on the numpy-discussion and python-announce-"
"list mailing lists. Look at previous announcements for the basic template. "
"The contributor and PR lists are the same as generated for the release notes "
"above. If you cross-post, make sure that python-announce-list is BCC so that "
"replies will not be sent to that list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:341
msgid "8. Post-release update main (skip for prereleases)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:343
msgid ""
"Checkout main and forward port the documentation changes. You may also want "
"to update these notes if procedures have changed or improved::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../RELEASE_WALKTHROUGH.rst:346
msgid ""
"$ git checkout -b post-2.4.0-release-update main\n"
"$ git checkout maintenance/2.4.x doc/source/release/2.4.0-notes.rst\n"
"$ git checkout maintenance/2.4.x doc/changelog/2.4.0-changelog.rst\n"
"$ git checkout maintenance/2.4.x .mailmap  # only if updated for release.\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release.rst  # Add link to new notes\n"
"$ git status  # check status before commit\n"
"$ git commit -a -m\"MAINT: Update main after 2.4.0 release.\"\n"
"$ git push origin HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/releasing.rst:26
msgid "Branch walkthrough"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:1
msgid ""
"This guide contains a walkthrough of branching NumPy 2.3.x on Linux.  The "
"commands can be copied into the command line, but be sure to replace 2.3 and "
"2.4 by the correct versions. It is good practice to make ``.mailmap`` as "
"current as possible before making the branch, that may take several weeks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:6
msgid ""
"This should be read together with the :ref:`general release guide "
"<prepare_release>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:10
msgid "Branching"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:13
msgid "Make the branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:15
msgid ""
"This is only needed when starting a new maintenance branch. The start of a "
"new development cycle in the main branch should get an annotated tag. That "
"is done as follows::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:19
msgid ""
"$ git checkout main\n"
"$ git pull upstream main\n"
"$ git commit --allow-empty -m'REL: Begin NumPy 2.4.0 development'\n"
"$ git push upstream HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:24
msgid "If the push fails because new PRs have been merged, do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:26
msgid "$ git pull --rebase upstream"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:28
msgid "and repeat the push. Once the push succeeds, tag it::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:30
msgid ""
"$ git tag -a -s v2.4.0.dev0 -m'Begin NumPy 2.4.0 development'\n"
"$ git push upstream v2.4.0.dev0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:33
msgid "then make the new branch and push it::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:35
msgid ""
"$ git branch maintenance/2.3.x HEAD^\n"
"$ git push upstream maintenance/2.3.x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:39
msgid "Prepare the main branch for further development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:41
msgid "Make a PR branch to prepare ``main`` for further development::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:43
msgid "$ git checkout -b 'prepare-main-for-2.4.0-development' v2.4.0.dev0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:45
msgid "Delete the release note fragments::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:47
msgid "$ git rm doc/release/upcoming_changes/[0-9]*.*.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:49
msgid "Create the new release notes skeleton and add to index::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:51
msgid ""
"$ cp doc/source/release/template.rst doc/source/release/2.4.0-notes.rst\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release/2.4.0-notes.rst  # put the correct version\n"
"$ git add doc/source/release/2.4.0-notes.rst\n"
"$ gvim doc/source/release.rst  # add new notes to notes index\n"
"$ git add doc/source/release.rst"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:57
msgid ""
"Update ``cversions.txt`` to add current release. There should be no new hash "
"to worry about at this early point, just add a comment following previous "
"practice::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:61
msgid ""
"$ gvim numpy/_core/code_generators/cversions.txt\n"
"$ git add numpy/_core/code_generators/cversions.txt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:64
msgid "Check your work, commit it, and push::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:66
msgid ""
"$ git status  # check work\n"
"$ git commit -m'REL: Prepare main for NumPy 2.4.0 development'\n"
"$ git push origin HEAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../BRANCH_WALKTHROUGH.rst:70
msgid "Now make a pull request."
msgstr ""
